Key Match Events: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander recorded 29 points in as many minutes
Chet Holmgren matched his point total with 20 points
Alex Caruso made 2 out of 3 three-point attempts
The Thunder made 14 out of 15 free throws in the first half
Houston Rockets went 9 for 19 inside the paint in the first quarter but just 6 for 23 in the following quarters
Pre-Game Insights: The Rockets were designed to combat OKC's strengths
Houston averaged the second fewest turnovers in the NBA (11.8) but still managed 16 turnovers in the game
Post-Match Reflections: Gilgeous-Alexander expressed pride in his team's effort after the comeback win
The Thunder's defense lived up to its suffocating standards
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was a 126-107 win for the Thunder
Jalen Green went 1 for 8 after the first quarter
Steven Adams played a season-high 16 minutes
